President Obama has announced his intent to nominate William S. Jasien for the position of Member of the Federal Retirement Thrift Investment Board. Jasien is currently the CEO and Managing Director of StoneHedge Global Partners, Inc. He has previously held executive positions at ING and served as Principal Deputy Assistant Secretary for Finance and Management at the Department of the Treasury. He has also worked in the Office of the Vice President and started his career as a Legislative Assistant to Senator Paula Hawkins.

President Obama has also announced his intent to nominate Dr. Brent F. Nelsen for the position of Member of the Board of Directors of the Corporation for Public Broadcasting. Dr. Nelsen is a Professor of Political Science at Furman University and has served as Chair of the South Carolina Educational Television Commission. He has also held various teaching positions at Furman University and was President of the South Carolina Political Science Association. Dr. Nelsen received his B.A. from Wheaton College and his M.A. and Ph.D. from the University of Wisconsin-Madison.